1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Here's what science actually says about vaccine efficacy vs effectiveness.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,000
Efficacy measures how well a vaccine works in controlled trials.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:08,400
Effectiveness?

4
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:09,600
That's real-world performance.

5
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:12,800
Imagine a vaccine showing 95% efficacy in trials.

6
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:15,200
But what about in everyday life?

7
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:19,600
It may drop due to factors like behavior or virus variants.

8
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:22,400
Studies show that effectiveness can vary widely.

9
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:27,600
For example, flu vaccines might be only 40% effective in a bad year.

10
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:32,800
Understanding this difference helps us make informed choices about vaccinations and public health.

11
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:35,200
Want to dive deeper into science?

12
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:36,800
Hit that follow button!
